  "A satellite navigation system uses Givens rotations to update a QR factorization in real-time. If applying a Givens rotation to zero out one entry of a matrix, how many rows are modified?": "",
  "None": "",
  "1": "",
  "All rows": "",
  "A Givens rotation operates in a single 2D plane, so it only modifies 2 rows (or columns) of the matrix. This makes it efficient for sparse updates in real-time applications.": "",
  "A machine learning engineer uses an orthogonal matrix to whiten (decorrelate) features. If the covariance matrix of the original data is C, what is the covariance after applying orthogonal transformation Q?": "",
  "I, pa": "",
  "C, pa": "",
